Below is the exact Jira behavior and how you can achieve syncing time tracking (Original Estimate & Worklog) from Sub-tasks ‚Üí Task ‚Üí Epic.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Why your Epic is NOT showing synced time

By default:
	‚Ä¢	Worklogs roll up only within the Story/Task hierarchy
(Sub-task ‚Üí Task/Story).
	‚Ä¢	Epics DO NOT automatically aggregate time tracking from Tasks/Sub-tasks.
Jira treats Epics as separate issue types and does not roll up time by default.

So even if you:
	‚Ä¢	Add Original Estimate in Epic
	‚Ä¢	Add Worklog in Task / Sub-task

üëâ Jira will NOT sync it unless you use Automation, Portfolio/Advanced Roadmaps, or Third-party plugins.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Solution 1 ‚Äî FREE & Recommended: Jira Automation Rule

You can create an automation rule to sum the worklog from all child issues into the Epic.

Steps to configure:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to:

Project Settings ‚Üí Automation ‚Üí Create Rule

2Ô∏è‚É£ Trigger

Choose:

Work Logged

This triggers whenever someone logs time on a task/sub-task.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Branch Rule

Add a branch:

For Parent ‚Üí Epic

4Ô∏è‚É£ Action

Choose:

Edit Issue ‚Üí Additional Fields

Add the following JSON (sums worklogs):

{
  "fields": {
    "timetracking": {
      "remainingEstimate": "{{#=}}{{issue.timetracking.originalEstimateSeconds}} - {{issue.timetracking.timeSpentSeconds}}{{/}}",
      "originalEstimate": "{{issue.timetracking.originalEstimate}}"
    }
  }
}

Or if you want the Epic to show total time spent of all child issues:

{
  "fields": {
    "customfield_10016": "{{epic.sum.timeSpent}}"
  }
}

(Note: customfield_10016 is the ‚ÄúTime Spent‚Äù field ‚Äî your field ID may differ.)

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Solution 2 ‚Äî Sum Original Estimate from tasks to Epic

Use trigger:

Issue Updated

Branch:

For Epic (Parent)

Action:

Recalculate field ‚Üí Original Estimate

JSON:

{
  "fields": {
    "timetracking": {
      "originalEstimate": "{{lookupIssues.Sum.timetracking.originalEstimateSeconds}}"
    }
  }
}


‚∏ª

‚úÖ Solution 3 ‚Äî Use Advanced Roadmaps (if you have Premium)

If your Jira edition has Advanced Roadmaps, time tracking roll-up is built in.

Go to:

Plans ‚Üí Create Plan ‚Üí Add Issue Sources

Enable roll-ups:

Plan Settings ‚Üí Calculations ‚Üí Roll-up ‚Üí Time Tracking

Then it automatically shows:

‚úî Epic Total Estimate
‚úî Epic Total Time Logged
‚úî Remaining Estimate

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Solution 4 ‚Äî Use plugins (if automation is hard)

Plugins that support Epic time rollup:
	‚Ä¢	Tempo Timesheets (best)
	‚Ä¢	WorklogPRO
	‚Ä¢	Time in Status
	‚Ä¢	BigPicture / BigGantt

These instantly aggregate rollups with zero setup.

